          <p class="card-body" style="margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 0.85rem;"><strong>All three US indices close at 2026 lows — third straight weekly loss.</strong> S&P 500 fell −0.6% to 6,632 after being up as much as 0.9% in early trading. Dow lost −0.3% (−739 pts) to 46,678 with 26 of 30 components negative. Nasdaq plunged −0.9% (−404 pts) to 22,312. <strong>Why the late selloff:</strong> Oil prices reversed higher in the afternoon, with WTI back above $98 and Brent above $103, crushing the brief morning optimism. Energy Select Sector (+2.5%) was the sole bright spot as $100 oil benefits producers. <strong>In Asia:</strong> Nikkei −1.16% as Honda's −6% plunge dragged the index; Kospi −1.7% as Korea's export-dependent economy faces higher input costs and global demand destruction. <strong>Key signal:</strong> Q4 GDP revised to 0.7% confirms the US economy was already stumbling pre-war.</p>
