          <p class="card-body" style="margin-top: 1rem;"><strong>The rate cut dream is dead — and a hike is now on the table.</strong> 10Y Treasury rose to 4.28% — up from 3.97% before the war — as oil-driven inflation expectations dominate. CME FedWatch shows less than 1% chance of a cut at next week's FOMC meeting. "Higher inflation expectations means higher yields, and rate cuts start to be priced out — that's the whammy," said Baird's Antonelli. <strong>The twist:</strong> Judge Boasberg just blocked DOJ subpoenas to the Fed, ruling they were a pretext to force Powell to cut rates — protecting Fed independence at exactly the moment markets need it. <strong>Mortgage impact:</strong> 30Y rate at 6.41% (+42bps in two weeks) adds $115/month to a $400K home. <strong>Fed meets March 18-19:</strong> Hold certain, but tone on inflation will be crucial. Some officials may now push for a hike given $100 oil.</p>
